<body>
  <h1>QuantumSort - Investor Pitch Deck</h1>
  <p><strong>Series:</strong> Pre-Seed<br><strong>Date:</strong> May 2026<br><strong>Contact:</strong> priya.shah@quantumsort.io</p>

  <h2>Problem</h2>
  <p>Logistics companies spend 12-18% of operational costs on route optimization. Existing routing systems become slow as route complexity grows, especially during peak delivery seasons.</p>

  <h2>Solution</h2>
  <p>QuantumSort is a quantum-classical hybrid optimization engine for large-scale logistics routing. It uses quantum annealing for the combinatorial core of vehicle routing, then classical post-processing to deliver deployable routes in minutes.</p>

  <h2>Founding Team</h2>
  <p><strong>Priya Shah, CEO:</strong> PhD Operations Research, IIT Delhi; former IBM Quantum researcher; published 6 papers on quantum optimization in logistics.</p>
  <p><strong>Arjun Krishna, CTO:</strong> Former Staff Engineer at Delhivery; built routing systems for 800,000 daily deliveries.</p>

  <h2>Traction</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Two paying pilots: Shadowfax Technologies and WareIQ.</li>
    <li>INR 5,80,000 MRR, roughly USD 7,000.</li>
    <li>23% reduction in distance driven in Shadowfax pilot.</li>
    <li>8 additional logistics companies on waitlist.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Business Model</h2>
  <p>SaaS pricing based on monthly base fees plus API calls. Starter begins at INR 1,50,000/month. Growth plan begins at INR 4,00,000/month.</p>

  <h2>Ask</h2>
  <p>Raising INR 4 crore pre-seed for quantum compute infrastructure, engineering hires, enterprise sales, and IP/legal work.</p>
</body>
